Pre-Game Insights: Gibraltar picked up a morale-boosting result in their final warm-up game on Wednesday when they beat Andorra 1-0 in a friendly.
Liechtenstein were on the receiving end of a surprise 1-0 loss against European whipping boys San Marino in Thursday’s Nation League group opener.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This will be the first meeting between the two nations since November 2022, when Julio Ribas’ men secured a 2-0 victory in a friendly.
Others: Gibraltar now launch their Nations League campaign, where they finished last in Group 4 of League C back in 2022 before suffering a 2-0 aggregate defeat against Lithuania in the relegation playoff in March.
Liechtenstein, on the other hand, were on the receiving end of a surprise 1-0 loss against European whipping boys San Marino in Thursday’s Nation League group opener.
